702587f-b.text:
(1)
Seventeenth Ave., east side, south of Cropsey Ave., showing the Fort Lowry Hotel, established in 1876 by Joseph L. Lowry.  It originally contained 20 rooms but was subsequently enlarged to 3000.  It was practically demolished by fire early in 1927.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, showing a close-up at a later date.
January 11, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
